nit: Vite automatically exposes `VITE_`-prefixed [env vars](https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode.html#env-variables) to `import.meta.env` as strings, so there's no need to manually inject `VITE_MARIMO_ISLANDS` via `define` config. 

Using `define` with `JSON.stringify(bool)` changes this behavior by inlining a boolean intead of a string, which can break type expectations (I believe TypeScript assumes `import.meta.env.VITE_*` values are string). 

We should update `isIslands()` from:

```ts
export function isIslands() {
  return import.meta.env.VITE_MARIMO_ISLANDS === true;
}
```

to:

```ts
export function isIslands() {
  return import.meta.env.VITE_MARIMO_ISLANDS === "true";
}
```

Split the two statements onto separate lines for clarity and avoid combining logic on one line. For example:
